ikki Varhely-Gillingham, Rosie Seitchik, Stacey Thomas-Muir, Nick Cannon, Ashley Sylvester, Lindsay Tuggle, Pete Cooksley, Chelsea Candelaria, Anne Chanthavong, Zo\u00eb Ritchken, Deena Katz, Erin Brady, Jeff Kmiotek, Lexi Shoemaker\n| {{nominated}}\n| style=text-align:center;\"| <ref>{{cite web|title=2020 PGA Awards Winners|url=https://www.producersguild.org/page/2020award_winners|website=[[Producers Guild of America]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200307135545/https://www.producersguild.org/page/2020award_winners|archive-date=March 7, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| [[Brunico Communications|Realscreen Awards]]\n| 2020\n| Talent & Studio-Based Competition\n| ''The Masked Singer''\n| {{won}}\n| style=text-align:center;\"| <ref>{{cite web|title=2020 Winners & Nominees|url=https://awards.realscreen.com/Winners/Winner/2020|website=Realscreen|publisher=[[Brunico Communications]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200405233615/https://awards.realscreen.com/Winners/Winner/2020|archive-date=April 5, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| [[Shorty Awards]]\n| [[11th Shorty Awards|2019]]\n| Best in Entertainment Sites & Apps \n| ''The Masked Singer'' Social Hub\n| {{nominated}}\n| style=text-align:center;\"| <ref>{{cite web|title=Best in Entertainment Sites & Apps|url=https://shortyawards.com/category/11th/entertainment-apps|website=[[Shorty Awards]]|date=January 28, 2019|archive-url=http://archive.today/poEjN|archive-date=April 15, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| [[Teen Choice Awards]]\n| [[2019 Teen Choice Awards|2019]]\n| Choice Reality TV Show\n| ''The Masked Singer''\n| {{nominated}}\n| style=text-align:center;\"| <ref>{{cite web|title=Here Are All the Winners From the 2019 Teen Choice Awards|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/awards/8527134/teen-choice-awards-2019-winners-list|website=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|date=August 11, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200215073036/https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/awards/8527134/teen-choice-awards-2019-winners-list|archive-date=February 15, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n|}\n\n==Spin-offs==\n===''The Masked Singer: After the Mask''===\n[[File:Masked-singer-after-the-mask.png|upright=1|thumb|Logo for the aftershow.|alt=refer to caption]]\nOn April 8, 2020, Fox announced that Cannon will host an [[aftershow]] of the series titled ''The Masked Singer: After the Mask'' on Wednesdays at 9:00 p.m. for four weeks starting on April 22. He will host the show from his house and discuss the outcome of the preceding episode with celebrity guests appearing remotely.<ref>{{cite web|last=Schneider|first=Michael|title=''The Masked Singer'' After-Show, Hosted by Nick Cannon, to Launch on Fox|url=https://variety.com/2020/tv/news/the-masked-singer-after-the-mask-nick-cannon-fox-1234574761/|website=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|date=April 8, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Roots|first=Kimberly|title=''The Masked Singer'' to Get Aftershow|url=https://tvline.com/2020/04/08/the-masked-singer-aftershow-nick-cannon-season-3-fox/|website=[[TVLine]]|date=April 8, 2020}}</ref> In the first episode, [[Kelly Osbourne]], [[JoJo Siwa]], Jeong, and McHale are all set to appear as guests, along with the eliminated celebrity with a performance.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thewrap.com/masked-singer-aftershow-after-the-mask-jojo-siwa-kelly-osbourne/|title=''Masked Singer'' Sets Alums Kelly Osbourne, JoJo Siwa as Guests for First-Ever Aftershow (Exclusive)|date=April 16, 2020|website=[[TheWrap]]|url-access=registration}}</ref> In the second episode, Ramsay is set to appear as a guest.<ref name=\"VAR Mar 26\"/>\n<!--\n{{Television episode ratings |width=85\n| show_timeslot = y\n\n| refs_col = y\n\n| title1     = After the Mask: The Mother Of All Final Face Offs, Part 2\n| date1      = April 22, 2020\n| timeslot1  = Wednesday 9:00 p.m.\n| timeslot_length1 = 4\n| rs1        = \n| viewers1   = \n| dvr1       = \n| dvrv1      = \n| total1     = \n| totalv1    = \n| ref1       = \n\n| title2     = After the Mask: The Battle of The Sixes: The Final 6\n| date2      = April 29, 2020\n| rs2        = \n| viewers2   = \n| dvr2       = \n| dvrv2      = \n| total2     = \n| totalv2    = \n| ref2       = \n\n| title3     = After the Mask: A Quarter Mask Crisis: The Quarter Finals\n| date3      = May 6, 2020\n| rs3        = \n| viewers3   = \n| dvr3       = \n| dvrv3      = \n| total3     = \n| totalv3    = \n| ref3       = \n\n| title4     = \n| date4      = May 13, 2020\n| rs4        = \n| viewers4   = \n| dvr4       = \n| dvrv4      = \n| total4     = \n| totalv4    = \n| ref4       = \n}} -->\n\n===''The Masked Dancer''===\nOn January 7, 2020, at the winter [[Television Critics Association]] press tour, Fox Alternative Entertainment and [[Warner Bros. Television]] announced that they had ordered a spin-off series, ''The Masked Dancer'', with [[Ellen DeGeneres]] as executive producer. DeGeneres had previously conducted ''The Masked Dancer'' as a recurring segment of her syndicated [[talk show]] ''[[The Ellen DeGeneres Show]]'', as a self-admitted parody of ''The Masked Singer''. DeGeneres stated that the show was \"gonna be just as fun and suspenseful\", but \"with a lot more [[krumping]].\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2020/01/the-masked-dancer-fox-partners-with-ellen-degeneres-on-the-masked-singer-spin-off-1202823169/|title=''The Masked Dancer'': Fox Partners With Ellen DeGeneres On ''The Masked Singer'' Spinoff \u2013 TCA|last=White|first=Peter|date=January 7, 2020|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thewrap.com/pug-almost-passes-out-playing-ellen-degeneres-latest-masked-singer-ripoff-video/|title=A Pug Almost Passes Out Playing Ellen DeGeneres' Latest ''Masked Dancer''|date=February 18, 2019|website=[[TheWrap]]|url-access=registration}}</ref> The series was expected to debut in summer 2020, however, due to the [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in the United States]], production has not yet begun.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/a-puzzle-all-pieces-broadcast-networks-scramble-program-an-uncertain-future-1288828|title=A Puzzle Without All the Pieces: Broadcast Networks Scramble to Program an Uncertain Future|last=Goldberg|first=Lesley|date=April 7, 2020|website=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]}}</ref>\n\n==Other media==\nOn February 12, 2020, it was announced that the show would be getting a live national tour with shows in over forty-five cities. Beginning at the [[Fox Theatre (Detroit)|Fox Theatre]] in [[Detroit|Detroit, Michigan]] on May 28, 2020, the tour will feature two celebrity hosts as well as a local mystery celebrity who is unmasked at the end of each show.<ref>{{cite press release|url=https://www.businesswire.com/news/home/20200212005953/en/MASKED-SINGER-Unveils-45-City-U.S.-National|title=''The Masked Singer'' Unveils 45+ City U.S. National Tour|via=[[Business Wire]]|date=February 12, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Schneider|first=Michael|title=''The Masked Singer'' Announces Nationwide Concert Tour This Summer|url=https://variety.com/2020/tv/news/masked-singer-concert-tour-summer-1203502739/|website=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|date=February 12, 2020}}</ref> The series has an online store where hoodies, coffee mugs, and phone cases, among others using the show's branding, are available for purchase.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://maskedsingershop.com/|title=Jazwares Announces New First Act\u2122 Karaoke Microphone Inspired By Fox's Mega-Hit Singing Competition Series, ''The Masked Singer''|website=The Masked Singer Shop|title=The Masked Singer Merchandise|access-date=April 20, 2020}}</ref> On February 24, 2020, toy manufacturer Jazwares announced they had partnered with Fox to release a ''Masked Singer''-inspired karaoke microphone under their \"First Act\" brand. The microphone will include a voice-changing feature and be sold at retail later in the year.<ref>{{Cite press release|url=https://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/jazwares-announces-new-first-act-karaoke-microphone-inspired-by-foxs-mega-hit-singing-competition-series-the-masked-singer-301009810.html|title=Jazwares Announces New First Act\u2122 Karaoke Microphone Inspired By Fox's Mega-Hit Singing Competition Series, ''The Masked Singer'' |date=February 24, 2020|publisher=Jazwares|via=[[PR Newswire]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200225165959/https://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/jazwares-announces-new-first-act-karaoke-microphone-inspired-by-foxs-mega-hit-singing-competition-series-the-masked-singer-301009810.html|archive-date=February 25, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.licenseglobal.com/toys-games/ny-toy-fair-jazwares-unveils-ufc-masked-singer-fortnite-and-all-elite-wrestling-toys|title=Jazwares Announces New First Act\u2122 Karaoke Microphone Inspired By Fox's Mega-Hit Singing Competition Series, ''The Masked Singer''|date=February 24, 2020|website=License Global|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200410063545/https://www.licenseglobal.com/toys-games/ny-toy-fair-jazwares-unveils-ufc-masked-singer-fortnite-and-all-elite-wrestling-toys|archive-date=April 20, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==Notes==\n{{notelist}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{Official website}}\n* {{IMDb title}}\n\n{{sequence\n|prev=''[[The World's Best ]]''<br />[[Super Bowl LIII|2019]]\n|list=[[List of Super Bowl lead-out programs|Super Bowl lead-out program]]<br />''The Masked Singer''<br />[[Super Bowl LIV|2020]]\n|next=TBA\n}}\n\n{{The Masked Singer (American TV series)}}\n{{Masked Singer series}}\n{{FOXNetwork Shows (current and upcoming)}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Masked Singer, The}}\n[[Category:2019 American television series debuts]]\n[[Category:Fox Broadcasting Company original programming]]\n[[Category:English-language television programs]]\n[[Category:2010s American music television series]]\n[[Category:2010s American reality television series]]\n[[Category:2010s American game shows]]\n[[Category:2020s American music television series]]\n[[Category:2020s American reality television series]]\n[[Category:2020s American game shows]]\n[[Category:American television series based on South Korean television series]]\n[[Category:Music competitions in the United States]]\n[[Category:Super Bowl lead-out programs]]\n[[Category:Television series by Endemol]]\n[[Category:Television series by Fox Entertainment]]\n", "name_user": "Heartfox", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Masked_Singer_(American_TV_series)"}
